.TH "dotnet-test" "1" "2026-01-30" "" ".NET Documentation"
.hy
.SH dotnet test
.PP
\f[B]This article applies to:\f[R] \[u2714]\[uFE0F] .NET 6 SDK and later versions
.SH NAME
.PP
dotnet-test - .NET test driver used to execute unit tests.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \f[V]dotnet test\f[R] command builds the solution and runs the tests with either VSTest or Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP).
The test runner you use determines the available command-line options and behavior.
.RS
.PP
Test runner selection is available starting with .NET 10 SDK.
In earlier versions of .NET, tests are always executed with VSTest.
.RE
.SS Choosing a test runner
.PP
To enable Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you need to specify the test runner in the \f[V]global.json\f[R] file:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
{
    \[dq]test\[dq]: {
        \[dq]runner\[dq]: \[dq]Microsoft.Testing.Platform\[dq]
    }
}
\f[R]
.fi
.RS
.PP
\f[V]VSTest\f[R] is a valid value for test runner.
It is the current default and can be omitted.
.PP
The \f[V]dotnet test\f[R] experience for MTP is only supported in \f[V]Microsoft.Testing.Platform\f[R] version 1.7 and later.
.RE
.SS Test runner documentation
.PP
The available command-line options, behavior, and capabilities differ depending on which test runner you use:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]dotnet test with VSTest\f[R] - The traditional test platform, available in .NET 6 SDK and later.
This is the default and only test runner in versions earlier than .NET 10 SDK.
Provides comprehensive test discovery, filtering, and result reporting capabilities.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]dotnet test with MTP\f[R] - The modern testing platform, available in .NET 10 SDK and later.
Offers faster test execution and more flexible test module selection.
.RS
.PP
[!TIP] For conceptual documentation about \f[V]dotnet test\f[R], see Testing with dotnet test.
.RE
